of
money, to which I readily agreed, and began
H 2
to look forward with hope to days of future
happiness
, and let me add innocence, for I felt
my heart
so
firmly attached to the generous
Rooksby
, as to render it
impossible
for me
ever to injure him even in thought. But, ah!
my dear madam, how
soon
