that would
consequently
ensue
on
a public
exposure
of my guilt, I therefore
told
Ramsay
I was ready to accompany him
wherever he
pleased
; but as to the
presents
I had received from Mr.
Rooksby
, I did not
conceive I had any right to take them with
me.
This was not what the wretch wanted
Horrible menaces and threats were
used
to
prevail on me to give him my
cash
and jewels,
I was intirely in the power of
these
three
wretches, nor did I dare even to call for the
