, thou much injured
woman
,
look there, (pointing to
Rooksby
)
You cannot
esteem
that wretch, and yet
you are linked to him for life, while the
only man capable of rewarding virtue like
yours: but no matter, 'tis I have done it
all, and I
deserve
to be unhappy.
I was greatly
distressed
to hear her talk
in this manner. But before I could
interrupt
her,
she
thus continued.
We are now, my dear
cousin
, hovering
on the brink of eternity. Which of us, or
whether any may
escape
the horrors of this
awful night, heaven alone can tell; but we
have both children.
Promise
