visitor
especially
a male one. It
may be
some
English
acquaintance I
must
leave you my Celia for a
short
time.
Oh heavens! how hard are my trials:
when will the throbbings of my
bosom
cease
!
When I left my pen and
descended
into
the drawing room, the door of which
stood
partly open, I
saw
sitting
with his back
toward
me, a gentleman in deep mourning.
He
arose
as I entered. Conceive my
surprize
.It
was Kingly.
Mr Kingly,
said
I, endeavouring at a
look of
composure
, while my pale
