, than the
rare and
expensive
exotics that
flourish
in
the green-
houses
of the
first
noblemen in
England. My parlour and dining room are
ormamented with pots of myrtle, geranium,
mignionet, and balm of giliad; the furniture
consisting
only of plain oak tables and neat
matted chairs. My bed chamber and that
of my child, is
furnished
